My ultimate UK Grand Tour

I was joined by @tomkahler on what turned out to be a unforgettable 'run and gun' trip around the top of Scotland and back south through the Cairngorms in the @astonmartinlagonda DB11 AMR exploring both familiar roads alongside some new hidden gems.

If you're able to dodge the weather, Scotland really does deliver at this time of the year. No midges, no tourists.. just a host of incredible vistas and unbelievable driving roads, pure bliss.

It really seemed quite fitting to be driving the best roads in Britain in a V12 Aston Martin GT car with its addictive symphony.

My first Porsche, the 981 Cayman S  with its naturally aspirated 3.4 litre flat 6. After spending most of my childhood dreaming of owning a Porsche, driving and owning this car was a significant moment in my life. For a lot of people sports cars are seen as status symbols, driven and owned by people with questionable motivation/mentality. 
For me cars are a complete obsession that drives me and motivates me every single day through both good and bad times, nothing beats the sensations of a naturally aspirated engine being rung out.

I hope that my old 981 is being appreciated and driven by its new owner whoever/wherever they might be. Hopefully it avoids lampposts and walls üòÖ
